text: Émile François Loubet (; 30 December 183820 December 1929) was the 45th Prime Minister of France and later President of France. He was involved in the 1899-1901 Boxer Rebellion and was President of France from 1899-1906 . ==References== Category:1838 births Category:1929 deaths Category:Prime ministers of France Category:Presidents of France Category:Politicians from Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes Category:People from Drôme Category:20th-century presidents of France Category:19th-century presidents of France
title: Émile Loubet
